  "texts": [
    "As a result, efficient training algorithms have received considerable attention.",
    "Further, recent work by Yu and Fazekas (2023) presented an efficient GPU implementation of all-pole IIR filters, evaluated exactly and recursively, with efficient backpropagation based on a simplified algorithm for evaluating the gradient.",
    "Similarly, accompanying their original contribution, Engel et al. (2020a) included an \"angular cumsum\" CUDA kernel, enabling phase accumulation without numerical issues.",
    "The development of open-source and efficient implementations of differentiable signal processing operations or their constituent parts is of clear benefit to future work, and thus we argue that this is a valuable area in which to direct future work.",
    "As we note in Section 5, there does not exist a unified framework for evaluating DDSP-based audio synthesisers, or in fact for synthesisers in general."
